Package: GenCorSeqSort
Type: Package
Title: Create a Feasible Correlation Structure Under Given Marginal Distributions by Sequential Sorting
Version: 1.0.0
Imports: matrixcalc (>= 1.0-3)
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0), stats (>= 3.6.2) 
Description: This package includes functions to generate mixed data that includes nearly all major types of variables (i.e., binary, ordinal, count, and continuous) when the marginal distributions and a feasible association structure in the form of Pearson or Spearman correlations are specified via an effective sequential sorting method.
License: GPL-2 | GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
Suggests: testthat (>= 2.1.0)
Author: Soumya Sahu [aut, cre], Jun Lu [aut, cre], Hajwa Kim [aut, cre], Yanli Gao [aut, cre], Pei-shan Yen [aut, cre], Jieqi Tu[aut, cre], Demirtas Hakan [aut]
